  "title": "She Stopped for Gas in Ohio. Won $500,000.",
  "script": "She stopped for gas! A woman from Nashville, Tennessee was on her way to a family reunion when she pulled into the S&G station on Fremont Pike in Perrysburg, Ohio, to fill up. At checkout, a $10 scratch-off caught her eye — Ohio Lottery, Bingo Times 50. She bought one. Scratched it in the parking lot. $500,000. She was in a random gas station in Ohio — not even her home state — and she'd just won half a million dollars. She drove straight to the reunion. Told nobody. The entire time. She later told lottery officials she wants to use some of the winnings to do something nice for her family. Half a million dollars in her pocket — and she didn't say a word. Did she tell them at the reunion?",
